A few years back when Sheperd was killed I believe I remember the news coverage of Phelp's crew outside the funeral with their picket signs and chants. If thats not causing shit I don't know what is, its sad when you give no respect to the dead or the grieving family.<br>
<br>
 What if it was someone's 82 year old grandmother who had a gentlemen friend after they were widowed. Lets say some pompous ass rounded up his friends and decided to picket the funeral or wake slinging insults because she was living with a man she wasn't married to. I don't know about anyone else but we wouldn't need police to remove them from the premesis we would be all too eager to take care of that ourselves. This coming from someone who chooses not to fight rather to turn the other cheek but sometimes someone will cross the line and its a matter of respect and integrity or maybe its the Irish in me we only need a half good excuse to drink and brawl. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
