<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I've lived in a small town in the south, so I have an understanding of what it might be like, if you were to oppose a preacher, of any kind for any reason.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Towns don't come much smaller than Folsom, Louisiana and I too know what its like to oppose a preacher especially a backwoods baptiste preacher. The preacher is the head of the town living like a king. Money in a collection basket seven days a week, grass mowed by parishoners(sp), food cooked for your family every day and a church filled with people on the edge of their seat waiting for you to grace them with your next words. I guess after a while they get to feeling like God themselves. Of course with that comes banishing people to hell when you have something against them or throwing them out the church. <br>
<br>
Case in point, a young man of the church had been dating the preachers obnoxious/demanding daughter, when he broke up with her he was thrown out of the church. The Preacher would only say someone here is not welcome in God's house and wouldn't give a sermon until the young man left. He was a good kid, gave his life to god, sang in the choir, most pleasant honest young man you could ever hope to meet but after that day he never returned to church even though his family still attends that church.<br>
<br>
So a big fuck you to the preacher. Even his daughter got one when she came into my store with an attitude one day. She didn't know who I was or that I knew who she was but decided to get a holier than thou attitude with me so Go fuck yourself princess there's the door. Needless to say I'm no longer employed there but that was for telling my supervisers to 'kiss my ass' on a write up. /wave Sobes<br>
